  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $S$ be a family of finite graphs such that for every $n$ there is some $G_n\\in S$ such that if the edges of $G_n$ are coloured with $n$ colours then there is a monochromatic triangle.\n\nIs it true that for every infinite cardinal $\\aleph$ there is a graph $G$ of which every finite subgraph is in $S$ and if the edges of $G$ are coloured with $\\aleph$ many colours then there is a monochromatic triangle.",
